author: Russell Brand
description:
Russell responds to Eddie Gallagher asking whether anyone in the UK is fighting back, arguing that resistance exists but stays fractured by years of cultural division, economic hollowing-out, and identity-driven politics. He traces the turning point from post-2008 populist anger and Occupy into a media landscape that shattered the old gatekeepers—then makes the case that politics is next, pushing toward localized sovereignty and decentralised decision-making as the only way out of permanent culture war.
